annotationA: EG:BACR7A4.16 protein; Mus81 is the catalytic subunit of the Mus81-mms4 structure-selective endonuclease that functions in DNA repair
annotationB: DNA repair and recombination protein RAD54-like; Involved in mitotic DNA repair and meiotic recombination. Functions in the recombinational DNA repair pathway. Essential for interhomolog gene conversion (GC), but may have a less important role in intersister GC than spn-A/Rad51. In the presence of DNA, spn-A/Rad51 enhances the ATPase activity of okr/Rad54
